 Parliament - The Portfolio Committee on Transport on Wednesday said that it is concerned with the violent nature of the protests in the transport industry. Committee Chairperson, Mosebenzi Zwane, said it was unfortunate and that the protest action could impact negatively on the public transport industry and the South African economy. “Transport is the backbone of our economy, safety on the roads ought to be guaranteed at all times. All stakeholders in the transport industry must to come together to resolve the crisis,” Zwane said. Several Trucks had been vandalised and set alight in the past two weeks in several provinces throughout the country. Although it understands the concerns raised by truck drivers the committee condemns any form of disorder, violence and vandalism on the roads. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 